genresAdvancedInfo.name: dutch classical piano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Dutch classical piano is a genre of classical music that is characterized by its focus on piano compositions by Dutch composers. The music is often characterized by its use of intricate melodies and harmonies, and the compositions range from solo piano pieces to larger works for piano and orchestra. Dutch classical piano has a rich history dating back to the 18th century and continues to be a popular genre in the Netherlands and beyond.
